 velocities would not erode the grains and release silicon in the\ngas phase. We therefore conclude that these new observations favor the\nhypothesis that L1451-mm would be at a very early protostellar stage, launching\nan outflow nearly on the plane of the sky with a higher velocity than is\nobserved.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 29 Aug 2022 13:55:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-09"}
